 to the perception of God as having some controlling influence. The following gives an idea of the ground to be covered: The patristic foundations of the Christian view of Providence; The medieval synthesis of ‘objective’ and ‘subjective’ views; Reformational and Early Modern: the shift towards piety; Modern Enlightenment: Providence and Ethics; Barth and the Sceptics; The sense of Providence in the Modern Novel and World.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aProvidence and government of GodxChristianity. 0aProvidence and government of God. 4aGebet. 4aGeschichtstheologie. 4aGlaubenserfahrung. 4aProvidence. 4aPrädestination. 4aVorsehung. 4adivine presence. 4ahistory of theology. 4aspirituality. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831103829760 cprintz978311031056640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311031064140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110310641423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110310641.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2015  aZDB-23-DGGb2015